---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout seo={{ title: "Editorial Standards", description: "Our editorial standards, fact-checking process, and corrections policy" }}>
	<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
		<h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Editorial Standards</h1>

		<div class="prose prose-lg prose-healthcare max-w-none">
			<p class="text-xl text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
				Trust is the foundation of healthcare journalism. Here's how we maintain it.
			</p>

			<h2>Our Principles</h2>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Accuracy first.</strong> Every claim must be supported by evidence — peer-reviewed research, official guidelines, or verified expert testimony.</li>
				<li><strong>Transparency.</strong> We disclose conflicts of interest, funding sources, and our relationship with MedBrains HMS.</li>
				<li><strong>Patient safety.</strong> We never publish content that could lead to patient harm. Health information undergoes medical review.</li>
				<li><strong>Independence.</strong> Our editorial decisions are not influenced by commercial interests, including our own HMS product.</li>
			</ol>

			<h2>Content Categories</h2>
			<h3>Professional content</h3>
			<p>
				Articles on hospital leadership, operations, technology, clinical practice, and regulation are written by domain experts with relevant professional experience. These undergo editorial review for accuracy, clarity, and balance.
			</p>

			<h3>Patient education content</h3>
			<p>
				All content in the Patient Education & Wellness category is:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Written or reviewed by a qualified medical professional (MD, MBBS, or equivalent)</li>
				<li>Marked with a "Medically Reviewed" badge showing the reviewer's name, credentials, and review date</li>
				<li>Accompanied by a medical disclaimer</li>
				<li>Referenced with citations to peer-reviewed sources where applicable</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Medical Review Process</h2>
			<ol>
				<li>Author drafts the article based on current evidence</li>
				<li>Medical reviewer (independent physician) checks for accuracy, completeness, and potential harm</li>
				<li>Reviewer approves, requests revisions, or rejects the article</li>
				<li>Approved articles are tagged with the reviewer's name and credentials</li>
				<li>Reviews are repeated if content is substantially updated</li>
			</ol>

			<h2>Fact-Checking</h2>
			<ul>
				<li>Statistics and data points must link to primary sources</li>
				<li>Medical claims must cite peer-reviewed literature or official guidelines</li>
				<li>Regulatory information must reference the specific act, rule, or notification</li>
				<li>Expert quotes must be verified with the quoted individual</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Corrections Policy</h2>
			<p>
				We correct errors promptly and transparently:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Minor corrections</strong> (typos, formatting): Fixed without notice</li>
				<li><strong>Factual corrections:</strong> Appended with a correction notice at the top of the article, dated and describing what changed</li>
				<li><strong>Significant errors in health content:</strong> Article is updated immediately with a prominent correction notice, and subscribers are notified if the error could affect health decisions</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Disclosure: MedBrains HMS</h2>
			<p>
				HealthPulse is created by the MedBrains team. We maintain editorial independence:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>HMS product mentions are clearly marked as promotional (CTA banners, not editorial content)</li>
				<li>Articles do not favor MedBrains over competing products</li>
				<li>Product comparisons, if published, disclose our affiliation prominently</li>
			</ul>

			<h2>Contact</h2>
			<p>
				To report an error, suggest a correction, or discuss our editorial standards:
				<a href="mailto:editorial@healthpulse.medbrains.in">editorial@healthpulse.medbrains.in</a>
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>
